close_reason: "Delivered deterministic agent-facing token budget regression gate across 14 CLI surfaces and wired it into static quality/release contracts; verified with unit tests, manual temp PM_PATH proof, full coverage, and CI static gates."
body: "pm-a22j records a ONE-TIME token-cost baseline for the before/after consolidation comparison. Nothing prevents the surface from silently regrowing afterwards — the historical growth pattern (each feature adds output, help text, contract entries) will resume unless cost is gated like any other quality budget.\n\nTurn the pm-a22j measurement script into a permanent regression gate:\n- Corpus of representative invocations run against a deterministic fixture workspace (help surfaces, contracts, and the hot agent read path: list/get/context/next/search in default, json, and toon).\n- Byte + approx-token measurement per invocation, compared against a checked-in budget manifest.\n- Gate fails on exceedance; budgets are only raised via an explicit commit that the diff makes visible (same discipline as eslint-suppressions.json max-17 and the LOC cap).\n\nThis makes 'EXTREMELY token-efficient output' an enforced invariant instead of a one-off cleanup, and gives the pm-n7rr consolidation a permanent ratchet: every help/contract shrink it ships becomes the new ceiling."
